               <head>Miscellaneous works on Sufism and visions, 2 items (a-b)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010117969">
                  <summary>Miscellaneous collection of works on Sufism and visions. Volume dated 1114/1702-3. Neat scribal nastaʿlīq by same hand throughout. Limited annotations in margins. Stamped (continuous) and Persian (discontinuous) foliation. Annotations in margins. Lacking original binding. Red half leather IOL binding, IOL stamp dated 14 May 1916. Early labels preserved at beginning. Folios bound; cropped, wormholes, later repairs, net overlay throughout. Condition fragile. Owner’s seal at beginning. See IOL Microfilm 490 for both items a-b. </summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1022-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="8r">ff. 1v-8r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item a. </p>
                        <p>Untitled treatise, endorsed at the beginning (f. 1r) as <title>Risālah-'i manāmīyah</title>, dealing with the psychological categorisation and spiritual significance of fantasies, dreams, and visions by the <orgName>Kubrāvī</orgName> Ṣūfī, poet and scholar, <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658919.0x000001 viaf_90062645" role="aut">Sayyid ʿAlī ibn Shihāb al-Dīn al-Hamadānī</persName>, known as <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658919.0x000001 viaf_90062645" role="aut">Amīr al-Kabīr</persName> (d. 786/1385), written at the request of associates as a response to the famous work <title>Ikhvān al-ṣafāʾ</title>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work is divided into three sections termed martabah. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end; see colophon to item b. 
</p>
                        <p>Fragile; severely worm-eaten. 
</p>
                        <p>IOL Microfilm 490.
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658919.0x000001 viaf_90062645">Hamadhānī, ʿAlī ibn Muḥammad, 1314-1385</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658919.0x000001 viaf_90062645">سيّد على همدانى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1022-item2">
                     <locus from="9v" to="29v">ff. 9v-29v</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657001.0x000001 viaf_295894712">Nūr al-Ḥaqq ibn Abū al-Majd ʿAbd al-Ḥaqq al-Dihlavī al-Bukhārī</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22187">Āgāhī'nāmah</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item b. </p>
                        <p>Ṣūfī treatise on the spiritual significance of visions and dreams by <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657001.0x000001 viaf_295894712" role="aut">[Muḥammad] Nūr al-Ḥaqq ibn Abū al-Majd ʿAbd al-Ḥaqq al-Dihlavī al-Bukhārī</persName>, the famous muḥaddis̲ (d. 1072/1661-2), written for the aid of associates. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work was completed toward the end of 1068/1658. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 29v): completed 1114/1702-3. 
</p>
                        <p>Annotations in margins, cropped. 
</p>
                        <p>Fragile; severely worm-eaten. 
</p>
                        <p>IOL Microfilm 490. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
